02/12/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Socialist Party (SP) leader Edi Rama is promising visa-free movement for the Albanian community living in Greece, saying this will happen in his first term, assuming his opposition party wins next year's parliamentary elections. According to media reports Monday (December 1st), Rama made the pledge in Athens, where he attended celebrations marking Albanian Liberation Day. He also told his audience he appreciates the economic aid that immigrants send to Albania, estimated at about 1.8m euros annually. (Shqip - 02/12/08; BalkanWeb, Shekulli, Gazeta Shqiptare - 01/12/08)
